<td>4 hours</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Over 2,000 words</td>
<td>Overnight</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<h2>Blog Writing Tip 15: Study What Works</h2>
<p>The best way to improve is to analyze posts that perform well. Save posts you admire. Study their structure, voice, and formatting.</p>
<p><strong>Questions to ask:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>How does the introduction hook me?</li>
<li>Where are the CTAs placed?</li>
<li>How do they use formatting to guide scanning?</li>
<li>What evidence do they use to support claims?</li>
<li>How do they transition between sections?</li>
</ul>
