<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How do I start writing a blog post?</strong></p>
<p>Start with research and an outline. Do not write from a blank page. A detailed outline with H2s, H3s, and bullet points for each section makes the actual writing much faster.</p>
<p><strong>How long should a blog post be?</strong></p>
<p>Standard posts: 1,500-2,500 words. Complete guides: 3,000-5,000 words. Match length to topic depth. Do not add words for the sake of length.</p>
<p><strong>How often should I publish blog posts?</strong></p>
<p>Consistency matters more than frequency. A sustainable rhythm of 2-4 high-quality posts per week beats sporadic bursts of content.</p>
<p><strong>Should I use AI to write blog posts?</strong></p>
<p>AI can help with outlines and first drafts. Human editing is essential for quality, accuracy, and originality. Use AI to accelerate, not replace, the writing process.</p>
<p><strong>How do I make my blog posts more engaging?</strong></p>
<p>Use active voice, concrete language, and varied sentence length. Include data, examples, and quotes. Write for one specific reader, not a generic audience. End with a clear action step.</p>
<p><strong>What is the most important part of a blog post?</strong></p>
<p>The headline determines whether anyone reads the post. The introduction determines whether they keep reading. The conclusion determines whether they take action. All three are critical.</p>
